WorkItem.Description:
Consider the chunk of ill-formatted TypeScript code:

```typescript
var defaultPath = path.join((env.HOME || env.HOMEPATH || env.USERPROFILE),
                                     CONFIG_FILENAME);
```

With VS Update 2 CTP, pressing Ctrl+K, D will format the `.ts` document like this:

```typescript
var dp= path.join((env.HOME || env.HOMEPATH || env.USERPROFILE),
    CONFIG_FILENAME);
```

The desired result is:
```typescript
var dp= path.join((env.HOME || env.HOMEPATH || env.USERPROFILE),
                   CONFIG_FILENAME);
```

Please remedy it before 1.0 goes RTW.

Thanks.
